other_tests.procedure_name: Drainage of Pelvic Cavity, Percutaneous Approach, Diagnostic
other_tests.findings: Mixed bacterial flora (>= 3 colony types), consistent with skin and/or genital contamination.
Normal uterus and endometrium; complex fluid collection in the left hemipelvis corresponding to the known abscess. Normal right ovary with a dominant follicle; left ovary normal.
